# SlopBuster — Constraint-First Development

SlopBuster enforces the constraint-first loop: **PLAN → GATE → APPLY → UNIFY**.
Every unit of work completes the loop. The Gate is not optional.

## Core Rules

- Before any SlopBuster work, read `.slopbuster/STATE.md` for the current loop position.
- **Never start APPLY** without `gate_cleared: true` in the PLAN.md frontmatter.
- If `# gate_pending:` exists in STATE.md, the Gate must run before anything else.
- Developer Gate answers are **never summarized or rephrased** — copy verbatim into `<constraints>`.
- `.slopbuster/STATE.md` is ground truth for loop position. When STATE.md conflicts with disk state, trust the disk.

## Loop States

```
PLAN ◉ ──▶ GATE ○  ──▶ APPLY ○ ──▶ UNIFY ○    Planning
PLAN ✓ ──▶ GATE ⚠  ──▶ APPLY ○ ──▶ UNIFY ○    Gate pending — APPLY blocked
PLAN ✓ ──▶ GATE ✓  ──▶ APPLY ◉ ──▶ UNIFY ○    Executing
PLAN ✓ ──▶ GATE ✓  ──▶ APPLY ✓ ──▶ UNIFY ◉    Reconciling
PLAN ✓ ──▶ GATE ✓  ──▶ APPLY ✓ ──▶ UNIFY ✓    Complete
```

## MCP Tools (if SlopBuster MCP server is connected)

- `slopbuster_gate` — enforces the Gate with a native elicitation form (5 questions)
- `slopbuster_status` — reads current loop state from STATE.md

## Override

If the developer types `override` when APPLY is blocked: proceed, log the bypass to STATE.md Decisions table with timestamp. This is a permanent record.

## Project Structure

```
.slopbuster/
├── STATE.md                     — loop position, decisions log
├── PROJECT.md                   — core value, stack, team
├── config.md                    — gate thresholds, feature flags
└── phases/
    └── {NN}-{slug}/
        ├── {NN}-{PP}-PLAN.md    — constraint-first plan
        ├── {NN}-{PP}-GATE.md    — gate clearance artifact
        └── {NN}-{PP}-SUMMARY.md — completion record
```
